Key Match Events: Mark Wood took 3 wickets for 3 runs
Jofra Archer took 2 wickets for 12 runs
England chased down their target with 101 balls to spare
Pre-Game Insights: England were in grave danger of heading for the same embarrassment as when they went to India, eight months ago, as the 50-over world champions
They now face what are on paper their two easiest assignments, against Oman and Namibia
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch looked better than Bridgetown, where England's previous games were played
The weather was set fair, with blue skies and a breeze
Others: The Omani national anthem was magnificent but on the long side
